APPLICATION PRIVACY STATEMENT
	- This privacy statement (“Privacy Statement”) applies to the treatment of personally identifiable information submitted by, or otherwise obtained from you in connection with the associated application (“Application”). By using or otherwise accessing the Application, you acknowledge that you accept the practices and policies outlined in this Privacy Statement.

WHAT PERSONAL INFORMATION DOES KID VIDEO COLLECT?
	- Devices information - device-specific information such as your hardware model, operating system version, unique device identifiers and mobile network information.

HOW DOES KID VIDEO USE THE INFORMATION IT COLLECTS?
	KID VIDEO uses the information described in this Privacy Statement (i) internally, to analyze, develop and improve its products and services, and (ii) as set forth below in the “WILL KID VIDEO SHARE ANY OF THE PERSONAL INFORMATION IT RECEIVES?” section below.

WILL KID VIDEO SHARE ANY OF THE PERSONAL INFORMATION IT RECEIVES?
	Personal information about our users is an integral part of our business. We neither rent nor sell your personal information to anyone. We share your personal information only as described below.

	- Agents: We employ other companies and people to perform tasks on our behalf and need to share your information with them to provide products or services to you. Unless we tell you differently, KID VIDEO ’s agents do not have any right to use personal information we share with them beyond what is necessary to assist us. You hereby consent to our sharing of personal information for the above purposes.

	- Business Transfers: In some cases, we may choose to buy or sell assets. In these types of transactions, customer’s information is typically one of the business assets that are transferred. Moreover, if KID VIDEO, or substantially all of its assets were acquired, or in the unlikely event that KID VIDEO goes out of business or enters bankruptcy, user’s information would be one of the assets that is transferred or acquired by a third party. You acknowledge that such transfers may occur, and that any acquirer of KID VIDEO may continue to use your personal information as set forth in this policy.
	
	- Protection of KID VIDEO and Others: We may release personal information when we believe in good faith that release is necessary to comply with the law; enforce or apply our conditions of use and/or other agreements; and/or protect the rights, property, safety of KID VIDEO, our employees, our users, and/or others. This includes exchanging information with other companies and organizations for fraud protection.

	- With Your Consent: Except as set forth above, you will be notified when your personal information may be shared with third parties, and will be able to prevent the sharing of this information.
	
CAN CHILDREN USE THE APPLICATION?
Our product is available for children. KID VIDEO creates a safe environment for our children to enjoy education, music, and entertainment content.

CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY STATEMENT.
KID VIDEO may amend this Privacy Statement from time to time without prior warning. Use of information we collect now is subject to the Privacy Statement in effect at the time such information is used. We will not reduce your rights under this Privacy without your explicit consent. We will post any Privacy Policy changes on this page.

QUESTIONS OR CONCERNS.
If you have any questions or concerns regarding privacy on our Website, please send us a detailed message at langthamyeuem19999@gmail.com. We will make every effort to resolve your concerns in a timely manner.	
